Reasoning: The paper discusses the consequences of a technological loophole in open access publishing that prevents the development of scientific data science, which involves the use of data analytic techniques to conduct meta-analyses and investigations into the scientific corpus. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), cybersecurity (cs.CY), cryptography (cs.CR), and databases (cs.DB). However, given the focus on open access publishing and scientific data science, cs.DL and cs.IR are the most likely sub-categories.
